# .gsiignore — gsi suppression rules
# Place this file in the root of your repository.
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.

# ── Ignore entire files ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# tests/fixtures/fake_credentials.py
# docs/examples/aws_setup.md

# ── Ignore a specific line in a file ────────────────────────────────────────
# config/local.py:10

# ── Ignore a pattern type for matching paths ─────────────────────────────────
# Syntax: [pattern_name] glob
#
# [secrets] tests/**
# [generic_api_key] docs/**
# [high_entropy_string] **/*_test.py

# ── Common suppressions ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment the ones relevant to your project:

# Test fixtures that contain fake/example credentials
# [secrets] tests/fixtures/**
# [secrets] tests/data/**

# Documentation examples
# [secrets] docs/**
# [generic_api_key] README.md

# Generated files
# vendor/**
# node_modules/**
